 BY Linus Chibuike SOME unrelenting #EndSARS protesters were, on Friday morning, forcefully dispersed by security operatives outside the gate of the National Assemly Complex in Abuja. Some of the leaders of the Friday protest were also reportedly arrested, following the demonstration. Gunshots were said to have been fired by the policemen, while protesters were also
teargassed to restore order in the protest area. The resultant clash caused gridlock in the adjoining roads. Publisher of Sahara Reporters, Omoyele Sowore, was said to have led Friday’s #EndSARS protest at the National Assembly Complex. The protesters had reportedly painted #EndSARS on the road to the National Assembly Complex during the procession. Details later… 